joseph john thomson

Definitions from WordNet

Noun joseph john thomson has 1 sense

Thomson, Joseph John Thomson, Sir Joseph John Thomson - English physicist who experimented with the conduction of electricity through gases and who discovered the electron and determined its charge and mass (1856-1940)

--1 is a kind of physicist

Definitions from the Web

Joseph John Thomson

Definition:

Joseph John Thomson was a British physicist who discovered the electron and conducted extensive research on cathode rays. He was awarded the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1906 for his work on the conduction of electricity in gases.

Parts of Speech:

Noun: Joseph John Thomson

Senses:

Scientist: A British physicist and Nobel laureate known for discovering the electron.
